{
 "name": "RPlog_Futile_Research_-_Reading_2",
 "title": "Futile Research: The Chyleni",
 "summary": "While reading on a bench in the Parliamentary District, the refugee girl Arise meets Kyrin Sh'vani, a winged Chyleni woman who alights nearby and politely strikes up a conversation. Curious about Kyrin's ability to truly fly, Arise draws her into talk of their lost homeworlds -- Arise's occupied Chandrila and Kyrin's distant, insular Chylene -- and of the atrocity at Cochran, which Kyrin witnessed firsthand. Kyrin shares hard-won convictions about good and evil, insisting that those who commit Imperial atrocities do so because they choose to, and that the first step to freedom is simply to keep thinking and refuse to surrender one's beliefs. Their exchange ranges over courage, the helplessness Arise feels as a child, and Kyrin's own resolve to fight injustice for the sake of others' children. The two part with mutual respect, Kyrin promising to carry Arise's words with her, and Arise heartened by the most encouraging conversation she has had in a long while.",
